The things people say we're useful for can be covered by 1 magician.  Extra magicians are a waste of bandwidth.<br>
<br>
Most mages have adapted to the BS -- they quit their character with 100+ days played and started over as a true melee class.  I think there's a better way.<br>
<br>
What's funny, though, is that this argument is between druids and magicians.  We should bring in the necros and we can all fight over the tiny scrap of usefulness we're allowed to have between us.  They can take away our DS ability and give it to druids, they can make mages better at giving away mana than necros, and in the meantime the &quot;holy trinity&quot; will continue to reign supreme with nobody encroaching on their horribly unbalanced monoply on raid usefulness.<br>
