<br>
For that matter give me a self mana spell equal to what VI past out to most casters in SOL.  Mask of Hunter/stalker (pffft what a joke).  Or now that no one wants POTG can we possibly get a single buff so that it doesn't cost me 1200 mana to buff just myself?<br>
<br>
Wanna talk nukes? Haha well if &quot;MOONFIRE&quot; weren't a myth (hasn't dropped on our server) i'm sure it will be every bit as resistant as this new Fire nuke is sure to be.<br>
<br>
Teleports? What's that, no needs a port from a druid anymore.  But hey this is one nerf I'm &quot;NOT&quot; going to complain about let the wizzies have the grunt work for awhile.<br>
<br>
Give us a real healing upgrade instead of Nature Recovery <br>
(hp regen that does stack with regrow).  Uh huh...well if anyone really wanted you to cast it on them that would be nice.  For casting time / recorvery time can keep it on any two people at once. Only useful place I've really seen to use it is enchanter types, tanks sure don't want you to take up spell slots they don't have to spare.<br>
<br>
Wanna talk druid class skills...yay I can now dire charm 1 mob out of every 30 or so zones because VI doesn't recognize an animal mob when they see one.  Yay I can AE regen or seasons because no one wants POTG anymore and it doesn't stack with AEOG.  Only really useful Class skill we got was Exodus but shhh don't tell VI or they might take that too.<br>
<br>
This post isn't meant to be a &quot;woe is me&quot; post, it's meant to point out that yeah maybe mages think they suck.  But druids are not in much better shape.  Though our nukes look nice they have huge resists and our heals are decent even though a paladin can almost out heal us now and do it on the entire group.<br>
<br>
Druids arn't exactly dancing in the street with the &lt;cough&gt; upgrades &lt;cough&gt; they've recieved the last year or so. Guess the point I'm trying to make is whether druid or mage most people who have played either for a long time don't play the class because it's so &quot;wonderful&quot; we play the class because we've come to love the class.  <br>
<br>
I'm sure people will disagree with some of what I've said but that's ok too we all have our opinions.<br>
